Trinidad and Tobago May Export Natural-Gas Technology to Ghana

-- B y   E d u a r d   G i s m a t u l l i n
-- 
2011-06-21T14:13:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/trinidad-and-tobago-may-export-natural-gas-technology-to-ghana.html
Trinidad and Tobago , the largest
producer of natural gas in South and Central America, may export
its expertise to  Africa .  The National Gas Company of Trinidad and Tobago Ltd. 
proposed building a gas transport system for Ghana National
Petroleum Corp. from its Jubilee field, Energy Minister Carolyn
Seepersad-Bachan said today in an interview in  London .  NGC has also proposed building a liquefied petroleum gas
plant in Tanzania, she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduard Gismatullin in London at 
 egismatullin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Will Kennedy  at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  